        <h2>Welcome to Our Bodybuilding Diet Plan</h2>
        <p>Building muscle mass requires not only intense training but also a well-structured diet plan. Our bodybuilding diet plan is designed to provide you with the necessary nutrients to support muscle growth while minimizing fat gain.</p>
        <h3>Key Components of the Diet Plan:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>High Protein:</strong> Protein is essential for muscle repair and growth. Include lean sources of protein such as chicken, turkey, fish, eggs, and tofu in your meals.</li>
            <li><strong>Complex Carbohydrates:</strong> Carbohydrates provide energy for your workouts. Opt for complex carbohydrates like brown rice, quinoa, sweet potatoes, and whole grains.</li>
            <li><strong>Healthy Fats:</strong> Don't neglect fats in your diet. Include sources of healthy fats such as avocados, nuts, seeds, and olive oil.</li>
            <li><strong>Plenty of Vegetables:</strong> Vegetables are rich in vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants. Aim to include a variety of colorful vegetables in your meals for optimal health.</li>
            <li><strong>Adequate Hydration:</strong> Drink plenty of water throughout the day to stay hydrated, support digestion, and facilitate nutrient transport.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Sample Meal Plan:</h3>
        <p>Here's a sample meal plan to give you an idea of how to structure your meals:</p>
