            </tr>
        </table>
        <p>Adjust portion sizes and meal timings based on your individual calorie and nutrient needs. Remember to consult with a nutritionist or dietitian for personalized advice.</p>
        <h3>Supplements:</h3>
        <p>While a well-rounded diet should provide most of the nutrients you need, some bodybuilders may benefit from supplements. Common supplements include whey protein, creatine, branched-chain amino acids (BCAAs), and fish oil. However, always prioritize whole foods over supplements whenever possible.</p>
        <p>Remember, consistency is key when it comes to achieving your bodybuilding goals. Stay committed to your training program and nutrition plan, and you'll see results over time.</p>
